item.title: [+1331] ‘Piracy Isn’t Killing Music’ Radiohead’s Guitarist Says
item.description: Last year, Radiohead expressed their growing discomfort with record labels that abuse copyrights for their own benefit, while harassing their fans. In a recent interview, Radiohead guitarist Ed O’Brien said that he doesn’t believe piracy is killing the music industry, but that the industry will kill itself if it doesn’t adapt to the digital age.

item.title: [+1161] AT&T Insider Reports Losing iPhone Exclusivity 1/27
item.description: Inside of AT&T, we are hearing that having the iPhone is hurting AT&T's image because they are the only company to carry it. We don't remember hearing about AT&T's "horrible network" before the iPhone--do you? The iPhone itself doesn't handle the switch from 3G to EDGE very well, so more calls are dropped when network congestion occurs.
